original: Österberg, Jobn Edvard, arkitekt, Norrköping, f. 25/11/04 i Norrköp. av Edvard August Ö. o. Jenny Elisabet Andersson. — Avg:ex. fr. KTH (A) 31. Anst. v. byggn:föret. o. arkit:-kont. i Sthlm samt v. Norrköp. stads ibyggn :nd, därefter prakt, arkit. i Norrköp. Utf. bost:hus o. aff :hus i ett flert. städer, biogr :lokaler, skolor, barnhemi, barnträdgårdar, yrkessk., verkst., stadsplaner. Lär. v. Tekn. Gymn. i Norrköp. Led. av Sv. tekn:-fören. fr. 32.
translated: Österberg, John Edward, architect, Norrköping, born on November 25, 1904 in Norrköping, son of Edward August Ö. and Jenny Elisabet Andersson. — Graduated: ex. from KTH (Royal Institute of Technology) in 1931. Employed by construction companies and architectural offices in Stockholm and Norrköping. Also worked for the city building administration in Norrköping, and later gained practical experience as an architect in Norrköping. Designed residential and commercial buildings in several cities, as well as theaters, schools, orphanages, kindergartens, vocational schools, workshops, and city plans. Also served as a teacher at Technical High School in Norrköping. Became a member of the Swedish technical association in 1932. Note that '\d\d m. partner's name' indicates marriage in the year 19xx.
